Notebook[{
Cell["RadarCoordinates", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"68c89ca4-840c-4def-a9c7-0269ee9c0a24"],

Cell["[LLM Generated]", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"65d37f3a-c3b7-4a7c-a0a8-83b3a7d1da97"],

Cell["\<\
RadarCoordinates[g, basis, v] returns the radar coordinates of v (distance \
vector to basis). RadarCoordinates[g, basis] returns the Association for all \
vertices, so RadarCoordinates[g, basis][v] is the natural operator form. \
Accepts InfraPoint[{\[Ellipsis]}] as the query point and as basis entries \
(aggregated by option \"InfraPointAggregation\" -> Min (default), Mean, or \
Max).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1f68f2ee-f4bb-43b3-a234-0e68697d6f09"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"58823412-ea7d-4701-b5a2-ff37a32236db"],

